examples.en: She hammered a nail into the wall.
The rain hammered down on the roof.
Many towns were hammered by the hurricane.
The coach hammered his message into the team.
College students regularly getting hammered at keggers.
The message must be hammered home that crime doesn't pay.
He hammered the ball into the goal.
British industry was being hammered by the recession.
The president has been hammered for his lack of leadership.
He hammered the dent out of the fender.
The batter hammered the ball over the fence.
His heart hammered as he choked out the words.
I hammered away at my writings again.
